<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-15T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-15T22:00:00-05:00" n="473" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/117a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-15T23:00:00-04:00">September
                                    15, 1942—11 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>229. Colonel McBride is leaving shortly for Liberia as a special
                            representative of the President. Please render him all possible
                            assistance in the performance of his mission. Colonel Upston of the
                            Office of the Chief of Staff will be with him, and it is hoped that he
                            may also be accommodated at the Legation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>